Package projects.phonebook.utils

Class KVPairList

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.phonebook.utils.KVPairList
  • public class KVPairList
extends java.lang.Object

    KVPairList is a simple linked list storing pairs of Strings. It offers constant-time insertion in the front and the back of the list, linear-time search and deletion and constant-time size querying for size and emptiness. To achieve constant-time insertions, it keeps track of both the first and the last node in the list. To achieve constant-time size querying, it keeps track of the list's count while insertions and deletions are made.

    Duplicate entries are possible in KVPairList. Additionally, KVPairLists are not sorted.

    Author:
    Jason Filippou
    See Also:
    KVPair, KVPairListTests

        public boolean contains​(java.lang.String first,

        Searches the KVPairList for the pair < first, second > and reports if it found it. There might be more than one occurrences of < first, second > in the list: this method searches for at least one.
